parameters.name: image.hires.enable
parameters.description: Should it be enabled at all

parameters.name: image.hires.oosFraction
parameters.description: How out-of-square will we allow the fixed area to be, 0...1

parameters.name: asset.use
parameters.description:
- ASSET_USE_UNDEFINED: Asset does not have use defined
 - ASSET_USE_INPUT: Asset is used as an input for the project
 - ASSET_USE_OUTPUT: Asset is an output from the project
 - ASSET_USE_INTERMEDIATE: Asset is an output from an intermediate step of the project
 - ASSET_USE_PROJECT: Asset is used as the project file for the project

Answer.description:
An Answer is a response to a Request. It is a set of Artifacts, which can be
of any type and forwarded to the client or the next stage.

AnswerMeta.description:
AnswerMeta is a set of metadata about an answer, usually the operating
environment.

index.title: Index of this artifact in input/output list

seed.title: Seed used to generate this artifact

uuid.title: UUIDv4 of the artifact, used for asset lookup

size.title: Size of the artifact in bytes

adjustments.title: Adjustments to this image / mask before generation

postAdjustments.title: Adjustments to this image / mask after generation

Artifact.description:
A tangible Artifact, such as an image, video, or text that is used for input
or output.

AssetUse.description:
AssetUse defines how the asset is used within a project.  This enum matches
the values the project proto.

 - ASSET_USE_UNDEFINED: Asset does not have use defined
 - ASSET_USE_INPUT: Asset is used as an input for the project
 - ASSET_USE_OUTPUT: Asset is an output from the project
 - ASSET_USE_INTERMEDIATE: Asset is an output from an intermediate step of the project
 - ASSET_USE_PROJECT: Asset is used as the project file for the project

ConditionerParameters.description:
Unused, but reserved for future use. Adjustments to the latents after
initialization.

DiffusionSampler.description:
DiffusionSampler identifies which sampler to use for Diffusion, and represents
the internal set of supported samplers.

models.title: models to use for this set

GuidanceInstanceParameters.description:
Parameters that affect the behavior of the guidance, typically used for CLIP.
We can specify more than one model, and the guidance will be a weighted sum
of the models.

GuidanceParameters.description:
Parameters that affect the behavior of the guidance, typically used for CLIP.
The omission of this field implies the default guidance of CFG.

GuidanceScheduleParameters.description:
GuidanceScheduleParameters are used to define a schedule for CLIP guidance, and
are used to define the behavior of the guidance over time. They are relative
to the total number of steps, and are scaled to the number of steps in the
current run.

enable.title: Should it be enabled at all

oosFraction.title: How out-of-square will we allow the fixed area to be, 0...1

HiresFixParameters.title: Parameters that control the hires fix feature

Prompt.title:
A Prompt is a special type of Artifact that is used to generate an output.
There can be multiple Prompts that affect the same output. Currently, the
only Prompts supported are:
  - Text (singular)
  - Init Image (singular, optional, type ARTIFACT_IMAGE, with init=true)
  - Mask (singular, optional, Artifact type ARTIFACT_MASK)

PromptParameters.description: A set of parameters for each individual Prompt.

Request.description:
A Request is a set of Artifacts, which can be of any type with model or
transform parameters. It is sent to the server, which will respond with an
Answer.

SamplerParameters.description: Parameters that affect the behavior of the sampler, typically used for CFG.

value.title: float value to apply on this schedule

ScheduleParameters.title: When does this schedule definition apply?

StepParameter.description: Parameters that apply to this block of the schedule.

Token.description: Generally, a GPT BPE 16-bit token, paired with an optional string representation.

Tokens.description: Sequence of tokens, paired with the id of the tokenizer used to generate them.
